  "decision_conditions": [
    "&lt;p&gt;In the absence of adequate information to demonstrate to the contrary, the proposed development would result in significant harm to the mature tree along the shared boundary between the application site and the neighbouring property of no. 75 Kyverdale Road. This tree contributes to the character, amenity and biodiversity of the immediate area. No on-site biodiversity improvements have been proposed to mitigate the impact on the existing tree. The proposal fails to comply with Policies G6 and G7 of the London Plan (2021) and Policies LP47 and LP51 of the Hackney Local Plan LP33 (2020).&lt;/p&gt;",
    "&lt;p&gt;The proposed development, by reason of its size, height, and position on the shared boundary,&amp;nbsp; would result in an increased sense of enclosure and loss of outlook for the occupiers of 75 Kyverdale Road.&amp;nbsp; The proposed development would therefore have a harmful impact on the amenities enjoyed by these occupiers and would fail to comply with policy D3 of the London Plan (2021), policy LP2 of the Hackney Local Plan (2020), and the stipulations of the council&#x27;s Residential Extensions and Alterations SPD (2009).&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;"
